          "title": "God's incomparability — the hymnic foundation (vv. 1-18)",
          "body": "The psalm opens not with crisis but with doxology. Ethan declares he will sing of chesed forever (v. 1) and immediately grounds that declaration in a double cosmic affirmation: lovingkindness will be built up forever, and faithfulness is established in the heavens (v. 2). This is not just abstract theology — it is the framework within which every subsequent accusation must be read. Verses 5-13 celebrate God's incomparability in the divine assembly and His sovereign rule over the chaos-sea and the entire creation. Verse 14 is the theological pivot of the praise section: 'Righteousness and justice are the foundation of Your throne; lovingkindness and truth go before You.' These four attributes — righteousness, justice, chesed, and truth — are not detachable from God's rule; they are its structural foundation. If God acts, He acts in accordance with all four. The lament will test whether God's apparent absence violates them. Verses 15-18 then apply the cosmic praise to the people who walk in the light of God's face — their strength, their joy, and their king all belong to the LORD. The praise is not abstract; it is communal and experiential."
